<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910305-0048</DOCNO><DOCID>910305-0048.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Fibreboard Corp.:   Legal Pact Set With Unit   Of Chubb; Stock Jumps $2</HL><DATE>03/05/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   FBD CB</CO><IN>CONTAINERS andamp; PACKAGING, BAGS, CANS, BOXES (CTR)INSURANCE (INS)PROPERTY andamp; CASUALTY INSURANCE (INP)BUILDING MATERIALS (BLD)</IN><LP>   Fibreboard Corp., Concord, Calif., said it reachedagreement with Pacific Indemnity Co., a unit of Chubb Corp.,settling all pending litigation related to personal injuryand property damage coverage.   Terms of the pact, subject to approval by the CaliforniaCourt of Appeal, call for Fibreboard to receive $35 millionin cash to be used on personal injury claims costs. PacificIndemnity also would be required to pay $107 million into atrust for future asbestos-related costs for which Fibreboarddoesn't otherwise have insurance.</LP><TEXT>   After the announcement yesterday, Fibreboard's sharesjumped $2 to close at $4.625 in American Stock Exchangecomposite trading.   Fibreboard, a building products concern, said court actionis expected to take several months, and approval cannot beassured. However, Fibreboard's chairman and president,Lawrence C. Hart, said both companies are &quot;optimistic&quot; thecourt will approve the settlement, which aims to resolve anestimated 75,000 to 80,000 asbestos-related claims againstFibreboard, as well as Fibreboard's struggles to get itsinsurance carriers to cover such claims.</TEXT></DOC>